{
  "texts": [
    "Secondly, we propose a novel observer design for ensemble models based on moving horizon estimation (MHE) [22], which enables the correct estimation of the states of all experts in the ensemble while enforcing state constraints.The proposed framework can be applied to the control of general dynamical systems, particularly those characterized by large and heterogeneous datasets, such as complex energy networks.",
    "In addition, the ensemble can be composed of any type of data-based model; in this work, we employ gated recurrent units (GRUs) within the family of RNNs, thanks to their strong approximation capabilities [23].",
    "Simulations on a district heating system featuring multiple operating conditions [24] demonstrate that the proposed Mahalanobis-based ensemble MPC significantly outperforms standard averaging and optimization-based methods of weight selection in terms of both economic performance and constraint satisfaction.",
    "Moreover, the MHE-based observer significantly reduces the output prediction error with respect to the ensemble model's open-loop predictions.",
    "Let N denote the set of natural numbers, R the set of real numbers, and R ≥0 the set of non-negative real numbers."
  ]
}